<?xml version='1.0' encoding='utf-8'?>

<activity xml:id="act-estrategiasSumar" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"> 

<title>Estrategias para sumar</title>

<statement>
  <p>Encuentra el valor de cada suma de cualquier forma que tenga sentido para ti. Explica o muestra tu razonamiento.</p>
  <ol>
    <li><p><m>325+102</m></p></li>
    <li><p><m>301+52</m></p></li>
    <li><p><m>276+118</m></p></li>
    <li><p><m>298+305</m></p></li>
  </ol>
</statement>

<solution>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ol>
      <li>427. Sample responses: I used base-ten blocks to make both numbers, then counted up the total.</li>
      <li>353. Sample response: I knew that 52 plus 1 is 53. I put that with the hundreds from the first number and got 353. </li>
      <li><p><line>394. Sample reasoning:</line>
         <line><m>200 + 100 = 300</m></line>
         <line><m>70 + 10 = 80</m></line>
         <line><m>6 + 8 = 14</m></line>
         <line><m>300 + 80 + 14 = 394</m></line>
      </p></li>
      <li>603. Sample response: I added the hundreds to get 500. Then I added the tens to get 90 because 305 has a zero in the tens place. Then, I added the ones to get 13. This made a new ten, which then made a new hundred. After the new hundred, there were 3 ones and 6 hundreds, which makes 603.</li>
    </ol>
  </solution>


<!-- ============================================================== 
   Notas profesor <prelude> (se pueden mostrar previo al enunciado)                      
===================================================================  -->
<prelude component="profesor"> 

  <!-- Estándares CCSS asociados -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="ccss-actividad-titulo"/></title> 
    <ul>
      <li> 
        <custom ref="ccss-addressing"/>
        <xref ref="ccss-2-NBT-A-2" text="custom">2.NBT.A.2</xref>
      </li>     
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Tiempo recomendado -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="recommended-time-titulo"/></title>
    <p>25 minutos</p>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Introducción de la actividad -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="narrative-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>The purpose of this activity is for students to add within 1,000 using any strategy that makes sense to them. The expressions in this activity give students a chance to use different strategies, such as adding hundreds to hundreds, tens to tens, and ones to ones, reasoning with numbers close to a hundred, or using a variety of representations. Students who use base-ten blocks or draw number line diagrams choose appropriate tools strategically (MP5).</p>
  </paragraphs>


  <!-- Materiales requeridos de la actividad -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="materials-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <!-- si hay materiales, crear los archivos -mat.ptx (para materiales de la actividad) y -matCentros.ptx (para mencionar los otros centros que se usan y para los que se necesitan materiales) y poner los materiales ahí usando los archivos de template. Después hacer xinclude  de estos archivos en la lista de materiales de la lección.-->
    <xi:include href="./act-estrategiasSumar-mat.ptx"/>  
    <!-- <xi:include href="./act-estrategiasSumar-matCentros.ptx"/>  -->
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Launch -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="launch-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Groups of 2</li>
      <li>Give students access to base-ten blocks.</li>
      <li>
        <q>Por un minuto, piensen cómo podrían encontrar el valor de cada suma</q>
      </li>
      <li>1 minute: quiet think time</li>
      <li>Share responses.</li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>


  <!-- Instrucciones para el desarrollo de la actividad -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="instructions-teacher-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <q>Con su pareja, sumen estos números de cualquier forma que tenga sentido para ustedes. Expliquen o muestren su razonamiento</q>
      </li>
      <li>5-7 minutes: partner work time</li>
      <li><p>Monitor for an expression for which students use a variety of representations, such as:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Using base-ten blocks</li>
          <li>Drawing a number line</li>
          <li>Writing their reasoning in words</li>
          <li>Writing equations</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>Identify students using different representations to share during synthesis.</li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>

</prelude>


<!-- ============================================================== 
   Notas profesor <postlude> (se pueden mostrar después del enunciado)                      
===================================================================  -->
<postlude component="profesor">

  <!-- Síntesis de la actividad -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="synthesis-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Select previously identified students to display their work side-by-side for all to see.</li>
      <li>
        <q>¿Cuáles representaciones muestran la misma idea o nos ayudan a encontrar la suma de la misma forma?</q>  (The base-ten blocks and equations show adding hundreds to hundreds, tens to tens, and ones to ones. The number line and the words both added on the second number to the first number in parts.)
      </li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Estrategias de acceso para estudiantes con discapacidades -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="accesibility-actividad-titulo"/></title><p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p><em>Engagement: Provide Access by Recruiting Interest.</em> Leverage choice around perceived challenge. Invite students to select 3 of the 4 expressions to complete. Encourage the completion of the last two expressions, as they will be the focus of the synthesis.</p>
    <p>
      <em>Supports accessibility for: Organization, Attention, Social-emotional skills</em>
    </p>
  </paragraphs>

</postlude>

</activity>